"{\"uid\": \"straitstimes.com-sport-curtain-falls-on-paris-puppet-theatre-to-make-way-for-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Choose edition  Search  singapore  asia  world  opinion  life  business  sport  Visual  Podcasts  SPH Rewards  STClassifieds  Paid press releases  Advertise with us  FAQs  Contact us  Sign up now:Get the biggest sports news in your inbox  PublishedMay 30, 2024, 08:55 PM  UpdatedMay 30, 2024, 08:55 PM  May 30 - Blue and pink lights lit the stage as the curtain rose at the Champs de Mars puppet theatre in Paris, with audience members welcomed to the show by a Guignol marionette against a background of cheerful carnival music.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 529, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"score\": 0.9999999998633484, \"rank\": 1.366663345327204e-10, \"text\": \"SPH\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\"}, {\"begin\": 147, \"end\": 156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"score\": 0.9604822703097123, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Advertise\", \"types\": [\"Q7377\", \"Q729\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\"}, {\"begin\": 407, \"end\": 412, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7502257310351848e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The puppet theatre, a fixture of the park since 1902, performed one of its final shows on Wednesday before it must close for the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 531, \"to\": 674, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is my life,\\\" the theatre's director Julien Sommer told Reuters.\", \"from\": 676, \"to\": 745, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 725, \"end\": 731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raymond_Sommer\", \"score\": 0.9999977371265368, \"rank\": 2.262876557618117e-06, \"text\": \"Sommer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q378622\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raymond_Sommer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raymond_Sommer\"}, {\"begin\": 737, \"end\": 744, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.773185708310687e-13, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Finding out from one day to the next that months later, we'd have to pack our bags, goodbye to 25 years of life - well, 35 years, since I started coming here when I was little - erased in two months for three weeks of sports, that's really unbelievable.\\\"\", \"from\": 746, \"to\": 1001, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Close to the Eiffel Tower, the theatre offers a classic repertoire of fairy tales such as Cinderella and Sleeping Beauty, as well as new creations, with a \\\"troupe\\\" of 400 puppets.\", \"from\": 1003, \"to\": 1182, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1093, \"end\": 1103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinderella\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.61330296778795e-38, \"text\": \"Cinderella\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinderella\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinderella\"}, {\"begin\": 1108, \"end\": 1123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sleeping_Beauty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0431834832473132e-13, \"text\": \"Sleeping Beauty\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sleeping_Beauty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sleeping_Beauty\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In January, Sommer said he had been informed by the city government that it was terminating its contract with the theatre, which will be closed from June for Olympic preparations.\", \"from\": 1184, \"to\": 1363, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1196, \"end\": 1202, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raymond_Sommer\", \"score\": 0.9999977371265368, \"rank\": 2.262876557618117e-06, \"text\": \"Sommer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q378622\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raymond_Sommer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raymond_Sommer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A petition to keep the venue open drew more than 13,000 signatures in one month.\", \"from\": 1365, \"to\": 1445, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris city council finally reversed its decision to terminate the contract, opting to suspend activity until at least October.\", \"from\": 1447, \"to\": 1577, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1451, \"end\": 1456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7502257310351848e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No reopening date has yet been set.\", \"from\": 1578, \"to\": 1613, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sommer says the city could have thought of ways to integrate the theatre into the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1615, \"to\": 1706, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's a shame to deprive tourists of Parisian life, of everything that's part of the charm of Paris, and to make something neutral, ephemeral, something without a soul,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1708, \"to\": 1886, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1745, \"end\": 1758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parisian_Life_(1936_film)\", \"score\": 0.715830738876978, \"rank\": 0.39697802197802134, \"text\": \"Parisian life\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q11424\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parisian_Life_(1936_film)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parisian_Life_(1936_film)\"}, {\"begin\": 1802, \"end\": 1807, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7502257310351848e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Wednesday, the puppets gave a joyful performance of the  popular fairytale Little Red Riding Hood.\", \"from\": 1888, \"to\": 1989, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1973, \"end\": 1983, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Riding\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Red Riding\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Riding\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Riding\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some spectators were saddened by the decline of puppet shows, once a popular spectacle in Paris.\", \"from\": 1991, \"to\": 2087, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2081, \"end\": 2086, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7502257310351848e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think there are only three Guignol puppet shows left in Paris,\\\" said Elvire Dauberville, who came to see Wednesday's show with her two grandchildren.\", \"from\": 2089, \"to\": 2241, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2148, \"end\": 2153, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7502257310351848e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Backstage, Sommer tidied up his theatre.\", \"from\": 2243, \"to\": 2283, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2254, \"end\": 2260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raymond_Sommer\", \"score\": 0.9999977371265368, \"rank\": 2.262876557618117e-06, \"text\": \"Sommer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q378622\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raymond_Sommer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raymond_Sommer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Touching his Little Red Riding Hood marionette, he bade the puppets goodbye.\", \"from\": 2284, \"to\": 2360, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We will come back,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2362, \"to\": 2391, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They are tough.\", \"from\": 2392, \"to\": 2408, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Do not worry, we will be fine.\\\"\", \"from\": 2409, \"to\": 2440, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"REUTERS  Theatre/plays  Mars  Music  E-paper  Newsletters  Podcasts  RSS Feed  About Us  Terms & Conditions  Personal Data Protection Notice  Need help?\", \"from\": 2441, \"to\": 2593, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2441, \"end\": 2448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"REUTERS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 2510, \"end\": 2518, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"RSS Feed\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reach us here.\", \"from\": 2594, \"to\": 2608, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertise with us\", \"from\": 2610, \"to\": 2627, \"entities\": []}]}"